    "narrative": "For Ghost Ride the WHIP on this April 14, **Corbin Carroll** represents our ceiling play with a 70.77 score, bolstered by a massive +16% park factor and an optimal #2 spot in the lineup. While he faces a stiff test against Rogers, his xwOBA remains elite and he remains our primary engine for the scarce SB category. **James Wood** follows closely at 65.98; he benefits from a rare \"slow delivery\" bonus against the opposing starter, which we project will increase his theft probability to 88%\u2014a massive edge in our 5x5 build. **Trevor Story** and **Josh Naylor** round out our strong starts, with **Trevor Story** capitalizing on a favorable 4.28 xERA matchup to reach a 61.82 efficiency rating.\n\nWe have maximized our platoon advantages, notably with **Max Muncy** and **Jose Caballero**, who both receive double-digit boosts due to favorable lefty-lefty splits and park dimensions. Our most difficult bench decision involved **Giancarlo Stanton** (49.48), who hovered near the threshold but ultimately lost his spot to the more versatile daily production of **Kyle Karros**. Despite **Giancarlo Stanton** benefiting from favorable wind conditions, the optimizer prioritized **Kyle Karros** and **Austin Riley** to balance our counting stat accumulation. Please note that **Seiya Suzuki** carries a minor risk warning; while he gains a +5% boost from wind, his matchup against Nola is tempered by an elite catcher pop time that may inhibit his base-stealing upside. We are staying clear of **Zach McKinstry** and **Alex Freeland** today, as both sit firmly below our 40.0 floor due to difficult matchups against Ragans and McLean, respectively.",
